DATABASE_PATTERNS = [
    {"topic": "db_normalization", "fact": "Database normalization: 1NF (atomic values, no repeating groups), 2NF (no partial dependencies on composite key), 3NF (no transitive dependencies), BCNF (every determinant is a candidate key). Denormalize for read performance: materialized views, computed columns, pre-joined tables. Trade-off: normalized for writes, denormalized for reads.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_indexing", "fact": "Database indexing: B-tree (default, range queries, ORDER BY), Hash (exact equality only), GIN (arrays, JSONB, full-text in PostgreSQL), GiST (geometric, range types). Composite index: CREATE INDEX idx ON orders(user_id, created_at DESC). Partial: WHERE status = 'active'. Covering: INCLUDE (columns) to avoid table lookups. EXPLAIN ANALYZE to verify index usage.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_migration", "fact": "Database migrations: Alembic (Python/SQLAlchemy): alembic revision --autogenerate -m 'add users'; alembic upgrade head. Prisma: npx prisma migrate dev --name add_users. Django: python manage.py makemigrations; python manage.py migrate. Flyway (Java): V1__Create_users.sql. Always: backup before migrate, test on staging, handle rollbacks.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_postgres_patterns", "fact": "PostgreSQL patterns: UPSERT — INSERT INTO users (email, name) VALUES ($1, $2) ON CONFLICT (email) DO UPDATE SET name = EXCLUDED.name. Pub/Sub: LISTEN channel; NOTIFY channel, 'payload'. Advisory locks: pg_advisory_lock(key). Partitioning: CREATE TABLE orders (...) PARTITION BY RANGE (created_at). Connection pooling: PgBouncer in transaction mode.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_redis_patterns", "fact": "Redis patterns: caching — SET key value EX 3600; GET key. Rate limiting: INCR user:ip:count; EXPIRE user:ip:count 60. Session store: HSET session:id field value. Pub/Sub: PUBLISH channel msg; SUBSCRIBE channel. Sorted sets for leaderboards: ZADD leaderboard score member; ZREVRANGE leaderboard 0 9. Streams for event log: XADD stream * field value.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_mongodb_patterns", "fact": "MongoDB patterns: Document model — embed related data that's read together. References for large/shared data. Aggregation pipeline: db.orders.aggregate([{$match:{status:'completed'}}, {$group:{_id:'$userId', total:{$sum:'$amount'}}}, {$sort:{total:-1}}, {$limit:10}]). Indexes: createIndex({userId:1, createdAt:-1}). Change Streams for real-time: db.collection.watch().", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_query_optimization", "fact": "Query optimization: EXPLAIN ANALYZE shows actual execution plan and timing. Common fixes: add missing indexes, avoid SELECT *, use LIMIT, replace subqueries with JOINs or CTEs, use EXISTS instead of IN for large sets, avoid functions on indexed columns (WHERE YEAR(date) = 2024 → WHERE date >= '2024-01-01'). Connection pooling reduces connection overhead.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_cte_patterns", "fact": "CTE patterns: recursive CTE for hierarchies — WITH RECURSIVE tree AS (SELECT id, parent_id, name, 1 as depth FROM categories WHERE parent_id IS NULL UNION ALL SELECT c.id, c.parent_id, c.name, t.depth + 1 FROM categories c JOIN tree t ON c.parent_id = t.id) SELECT * FROM tree ORDER BY depth, name. Materialized CTE in PostgreSQL 12+: WITH cte AS MATERIALIZED (...).", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_window_functions", "fact": "Window functions: ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY dept ORDER BY salary DESC) as rank — assigns sequential numbers. RANK() leaves gaps for ties, DENSE_RANK() doesn't. LAG(salary, 1) OVER(ORDER BY hire_date) — previous row value. Running total: SUM(amount) OVER(ORDER BY date ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW). NTILE(4) for quartiles.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_nosql_patterns", "fact": "NoSQL patterns: Key-Value (Redis, DynamoDB) — session store, cache, counters. Document (MongoDB, Firestore) — flexible schema, nested data. Column-Family (Cassandra, ScyllaDB) — time-series, write-heavy. Graph (Neo4j, Neptune) — relationships, social networks. Choose based on: access patterns, consistency needs, scale requirements. CAP theorem: pick 2 of consistency, availability, partition tolerance.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_sharding", "fact": "Database sharding: horizontal partitioning across servers. Shard key selection is critical — high cardinality, even distribution, query alignment. Strategies: range-based (date ranges), hash-based (hash(user_id) % N), directory-based (lookup table). Cross-shard queries are expensive. Vitess for MySQL sharding, Citus for PostgreSQL. Alternative: read replicas for read scaling.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "db_backup_strategies", "fact": "Database backup strategies: Full backup (complete copy, large but simple), Incremental (changes since last backup, fast but complex restore), WAL archiving (PostgreSQL continuous archiving, point-in-time recovery). pg_dump for logical backup, pg_basebackup for physical. Test restores regularly. 3-2-1 rule: 3 copies, 2 media types, 1 offsite.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "db_connection_pooling", "fact": "Connection pooling: PgBouncer (PostgreSQL, lightweight, transaction/session/statement modes), HikariCP (Java, fastest JVM pool), SQLAlchemy pool (Python, create_engine(pool_size=20, max_overflow=10)). Pool sizing: connections = (cpu_cores * 2) + disk_spindles. Too many connections: context switching overhead. Too few: request queuing.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "db_elasticsearch", "fact": "Elasticsearch patterns: index with mappings (text for full-text, keyword for exact match). Query DSL: { 'query': { 'bool': { 'must': [{ 'match': { 'title': 'search term' } }], 'filter': [{ 'range': { 'date': { 'gte': '2024-01-01' } } }] } } }. Aggregations for analytics. Bulk API for indexing. Index aliases for zero-downtime reindexing.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "db_time_series", "fact": "Time-series databases: TimescaleDB (PostgreSQL extension) — hypertables with automatic partitioning by time. InfluxDB — line protocol, Flux query language. Retention policies for automatic data expiry. Continuous aggregates for pre-computed rollups. Compression for old data. Common: IoT sensors, metrics, financial data, logs.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "db_graph_patterns", "fact": "Graph database patterns (Neo4j): CREATE (alice:Person {name:'Alice'})-[:KNOWS]->(bob:Person {name:'Bob'}). MATCH (p:Person)-[:KNOWS*1..3]->(friend) WHERE p.name = 'Alice' RETURN friend.name — finds friends up to 3 hops. PageRank, community detection, shortest path algorithms built-in. Use cases: social networks, recommendation engines, fraud detection, knowledge graphs.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "db_sqlite_patterns", "fact": "SQLite patterns: WAL mode for concurrent reads — PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL. ATTACH DATABASE 'other.db' AS other for cross-database queries. JSON1 extension: json_extract(col, '$.key'), json_each(). FTS5 full-text: CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE docs USING fts5(title, body); SELECT * FROM docs WHERE docs MATCH 'search term'. Perfect for: embedded apps, mobile, CLI tools, testing.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "db_data_modeling", "fact": "Data modeling: Entity-Relationship Diagram (ERD) — entities (tables), attributes (columns), relationships (1:1, 1:N, M:N). Junction/bridge table for M:N. Surrogate keys (auto-increment/UUID) vs natural keys. Soft deletes (deleted_at timestamp) vs hard deletes. Audit columns: created_at, updated_at, created_by. Version column for optimistic locking.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_transactions", "fact": "Database transactions: ACID — Atomicity (all or nothing), Consistency (valid state), Isolation (concurrent safety), Durability (survives crash). Isolation levels: READ UNCOMMITTED (dirty reads), READ COMMITTED (no dirty reads), REPEATABLE READ (no non-repeatable reads), SERIALIZABLE (no phantom reads). PostgreSQL default: READ COMMITTED. Use SELECT FOR UPDATE for row-level locks.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "db_replication", "fact": "Database replication: Primary-Replica (master-slave) — writes to primary, reads from replicas. Synchronous (strong consistency, higher latency) vs asynchronous (eventual consistency, lower latency). Streaming replication in PostgreSQL. Multi-primary for write scaling (conflict resolution needed). Logical replication for selective table sync. Failover: automatic with tools like Patroni.", "confidence": 0.9},
]

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
# COLLECTION 5 — DEVOPS PATTERNS (20 entries)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

DEVOPS_PATTERNS = [
    {"topic": "dockerfile_best", "fact": "Dockerfile best practices: multi-stage builds — FROM node:20 AS build; WORKDIR /app; COPY package*.json .; RUN npm ci; COPY . .; RUN npm run build; FROM node:20-slim; COPY --from=build /app/dist ./dist; CMD ['node', 'dist/index.js']. Use .dockerignore. Pin versions. Non-root user: RUN adduser --disabled-password app; USER app. Layer caching: COPY package.json before source.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "docker_compose", "fact": "Docker Compose patterns: services: app: build: .; ports: ['3000:3000']; environment: DATABASE_URL: postgres://user:pass@db:5432/app; depends_on: db: condition: service_healthy; db: image: postgres:16; healthcheck: test: ['CMD-SHELL', 'pg_isready']; interval: 5s; volumes: [pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data]; redis: image: redis:7-alpine; volumes: pgdata:.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "github_actions", "fact": "GitHub Actions CI/CD: name: CI; on: push: branches: [main]; pull_request:; jobs: test: runs-on: ubuntu-latest; steps: - uses: actions/checkout@v4; - uses: actions/setup-node@v4; with: node-version: 20; - run: npm ci; - run: npm test; deploy: needs: test; if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'; runs-on: ubuntu-latest; steps: - uses: actions/checkout@v4; - run: docker build -t app .; - run: docker push registry/app:latest.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "github_actions_matrix", "fact": "GitHub Actions matrix strategy: strategy: matrix: node-version: [18, 20, 22]; os: [ubuntu-latest, macos-latest]; steps: - uses: actions/setup-node@v4; with: node-version: ${{ matrix.node-version }}. Caching: - uses: actions/cache@v4; with: path: ~/.npm; key: ${{ runner.os }}-node-${{ hashFiles('**/package-lock.json') }}.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "k8s_helm", "fact": "Kubernetes Helm chart: Chart.yaml (name, version), values.yaml (configurable params), templates/ (deployment.yaml, service.yaml, ingress.yaml). values.yaml: replicaCount: 3; image: repository: myapp; tag: latest; service: type: ClusterIP; port: 80. Template: replicas: {{ .Values.replicaCount }}. helm install myapp ./chart; helm upgrade myapp ./chart; helm rollback myapp 1.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "k8s_manifests", "fact": "Kubernetes core manifests: Deployment (manages pods), Service (network endpoint), ConfigMap (config data), Secret (sensitive data), Ingress (HTTP routing), HPA (auto-scaling). kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml. kubectl get pods. kubectl logs pod-name. kubectl exec -it pod-name -- sh. kubectl rollout status/undo deployment/name. Namespace isolation: kubectl create namespace staging.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "terraform_iac", "fact": "Terraform IaC: provider 'aws' { region = 'us-east-1' }; resource 'aws_instance' 'web' { ami = 'ami-xxx'; instance_type = 't3.micro'; tags = { Name = 'web-server' } }. terraform init/plan/apply/destroy. State: terraform.tfstate (store remotely in S3+DynamoDB). Modules: module 'vpc' { source = './modules/vpc' }. Variables: variable 'env' { default = 'dev' }.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "nginx_config", "fact": "Nginx configuration: server { listen 80; server_name example.com; location / { proxy_pass http://app:3000; proxy_set_header Host $host; proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr; } location /api { proxy_pass http://api:8000; } location /static { alias /var/www/static; expires 30d; } }. SSL: listen 443 ssl; ssl_certificate /etc/ssl/cert.pem; ssl_certificate_key /etc/ssl/key.pem.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "monitoring_stack", "fact": "Monitoring stack: Prometheus (metrics collection, PromQL queries, alerting rules) + Grafana (dashboards, visualization). Application metrics: prometheus_client (Python), prom-client (Node). Key metrics: RED (Rate, Errors, Duration) for services, USE (Utilization, Saturation, Errors) for resources. Alert example: rate(http_requests_total{status=~'5..'}[5m]) > 0.05.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "logging_stack", "fact": "Logging stack: ELK (Elasticsearch + Logstash + Kibana) or Loki + Grafana. Structured logging: JSON format with timestamp, level, message, request_id, user_id. Python: structlog or loguru. Node: pino or winston. Correlation IDs across services. Log levels: DEBUG < INFO < WARNING < ERROR < CRITICAL. Don't log PII or secrets. Retention policy: 30 days hot, 90 days warm, 1 year cold.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "ci_cd_pipeline", "fact": "CI/CD pipeline stages: 1) Lint (eslint, ruff, clippy), 2) Type check (tsc, mypy), 3) Unit tests, 4) Build (docker build, npm build), 5) Integration tests, 6) Security scan (Snyk, Trivy), 7) Deploy to staging, 8) E2E tests on staging, 9) Deploy to production (blue-green or canary), 10) Smoke tests. Rollback: automatic on health check failure.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "gitops", "fact": "GitOps: ArgoCD or Flux watches a Git repo for Kubernetes manifests. Changes to manifests trigger automatic deployment. Pull-based model (cluster pulls from Git, no CI pushing to cluster). Environments: separate branches or directories (envs/staging/, envs/production/). Sealed Secrets for encrypted secrets in Git. Kustomize for environment-specific overlays.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "container_security", "fact": "Container security: scan images with Trivy/Snyk (trivy image myapp:latest). Use minimal base images (alpine, distroless). Non-root user in Dockerfile. Read-only filesystem: docker run --read-only. No secrets in images — use runtime env vars or secret managers. Network policies in Kubernetes. Pod Security Standards: restricted profile. Supply chain: sign images with cosign.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "load_balancing", "fact": "Load balancing strategies: Round Robin (equal distribution), Least Connections (fewest active), IP Hash (sticky sessions), Weighted (proportional to capacity). AWS ALB for HTTP/HTTPS with path-based routing. HAProxy for TCP/HTTP with health checks. Kubernetes Service (kube-proxy iptables/IPVS). Rate limiting: token bucket algorithm. Circuit breaker: open/half-open/closed states.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "secrets_management", "fact": "Secrets management: HashiCorp Vault (dynamic secrets, encryption as a service, PKI). AWS Secrets Manager/Parameter Store. Azure Key Vault. GCP Secret Manager. Kubernetes: external-secrets-operator syncs from Vault/AWS to K8s Secrets. Never commit secrets to Git. .env files for local dev only (add to .gitignore). Rotate secrets regularly. Least privilege access.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "zero_downtime_deploy", "fact": "Zero-downtime deployment: Blue-Green (two identical environments, switch traffic). Rolling update (gradually replace instances). Canary (route small % to new version, monitor, then full rollout). Kubernetes: maxSurge: 1, maxUnavailable: 0. Database migrations must be backward-compatible. Feature flags for gradual rollout. Health check endpoint: /healthz.", "confidence": 0.9},
    {"topic": "makefile_patterns", "fact": "Makefile patterns: .PHONY: test lint build deploy; test: pytest -v --cov=src; lint: ruff check src && mypy src; build: docker build -t app:$(VERSION) .; deploy: kubectl apply -f k8s/; dev: docker compose up -d && uvicorn main:app --reload; clean: find . -name '__pycache__' -exec rm -rf {} +; help: @grep -E '^[a-zA-Z_-]+:.*?## .*$$' $(MAKEFILE_LIST) | awk 'BEGIN {FS = \":.*?## \"}; {printf \"%-15s %s\\n\", $$1, $$2}'.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "pre_commit_hooks", "fact": "Pre-commit hooks: .pre-commit-config.yaml — repos: - repo: https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks; hooks: - id: trailing-whitespace; - id: check-yaml; - repo: https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff-pre-commit; hooks: - id: ruff; - id: ruff-format. Install: pre-commit install. Run all: pre-commit run --all-files. Prevents bad commits from entering the repo.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "env_management", "fact": "Environment management: .env for local development (never commit). .env.example with placeholder values (commit this). dotenv library loads .env into process.env / os.environ. Docker: env_file: .env in compose. Kubernetes: ConfigMap for non-sensitive, Secret for sensitive. 12-Factor App: store config in environment. Validate required vars at startup.", "confidence": 0.95},
    {"topic": "git_workflow", "fact": "Git workflow: trunk-based development — short-lived feature branches, merge to main frequently. Branch naming: feature/add-auth, fix/login-bug, chore/update-deps. Conventional commits: feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:, refactor:, test:. Squash merge for clean history. Semantic versioning: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH. Changelog: auto-generate from conventional commits.", "confidence": 0.95},
]

